  <Content>&lt;b&gt;Age of Fire&lt;/b&gt;

Aislings,

Mundanes and Aislings of Hwarone wanted to venerate the Fire Spirit in appreciation and celebration of over 60 Deoches of safety and prosperity in the city. Hwarone, located under a massive volcano in Medenia, has been protected from lava flows and ash. King Bruce, in the spirit of amicable international relations with the Medenian nation, has decided to also mark the occasion with fireworks, merriment, and gifts for guests. Which, aha, means good old Bruce is letting the wizards drink for a time, aha!

The celebration marks the beginning of the Age of Fire which will be the first in the �����������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������������cycle of Medenian Spirits. Longer than the Temuairian octave, a new elemental spirit will be honored each eight deoch in the Medenian cycle.

Temuairian or Medenian citizens alike are welcome to join the festivities in Loures any time for those of us who, aha, lack the stamina to last the entire shindig, aha!

- &lt;i&gt;Jean&lt;/i&gt;


